[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.450] Purpose:
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.450] + Optionally join trials with given run_name and index ranges [ga,gb] [ta,tb]...
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.450] + ...Or run on any individual file.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.450] + Optionally apply demultiplexing corrections.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.450] + Optionally apply band-pass and global CAR filters.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] + Optionally edit out saturation artifacts.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] + Optionally extract tables of sync waveform edge times to drive TPrime.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] + Optionally extract tables of other nonneural event times to be aligned with spikes.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] + Optionally join the above outputs across different runs (supercat feature).

[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] Output:
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] + Results are placed next to source, named like this, with t-index = tcat:
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.451] +    path/run_name_g5_tcat.imec1.ap.bin.
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.452] + Errors and run messages are appended to CatGT.log in the current working directory.

[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.452] Usage:
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.452] >CatGT -dir=data_dir -run=run_name -g=ga,gb -t=ta,tb <which streams> [ options ]

[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.452] Which streams:
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.452] -ni                      ;required to process ni stream
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -ob                      ;required to process ob streams
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -ap                      ;required to process ap streams
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -lf                      ;required to process lf streams
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -obx=0,3:5               ;if -ob process these OneBoxes
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -prb_3A                  ;if -ap or -lf process 3A-style probe files, e.g., run_name_g0_t0.imec.ap.bin
[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.453] -prb=0,3:5               ;if -ap or -lf AND !prb_3A process these probes

[Thd 40820 CPU 2 6/16/24 11:28:06.454] Options:
